/// section
h1: About The Long Read

col:
  p: The Long Read was started in 2021 by two journalists who were tired of writing to SEO briefs. We publish one to two pieces a week — long-form reported stories and essays about technology and the built environment.

col:
  p: We have no investors, no editorial board, and no algorithmic pressures. If something takes six months to report properly, we take six months.

/// section align:center
h2: Our editorial standards

col:
  icon: bi bi-incognito
  h3: No tracking
  p: We collect no analytics, no behavioral data, no ad pixels. Your reading is your own.

col:
  icon: bi bi-journal-check
  h3: Named sources
  p: We don't publish anonymously sourced claims without a documented reason. We always try to give subjects the chance to respond.

col:
  icon: bi bi-archive
  h3: Everything stays up
  p: We don't delete stories. If we get something wrong, we publish a correction and leave both up.


